{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutexProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"text":"PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"}]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":" can be statically allocated","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a version of our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"give_me_next_number()"},{"type":"text","text":" example using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a GStaticMutex:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want to require prior calling to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":", because your code"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_mutex_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" and thus "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", as that requires a prior call to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"text":". In these cases you can also use a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It must be initialized with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_mutex_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" before using it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and freed with with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_mutex_free()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when not needed anymore to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"free up any allocated resources.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Even though ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"platforms."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be used even if "},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()"},{"text":" which does nothing but returning ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticMutex"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"StaticMutexProtocol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutexProtocol"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutexProtocol"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib19StaticMutexProtocolP","symbolKi